    <title>Exponential Varieties</title>
    <summary>  Exponential varieties arise from exponential families in statistics. These
real algebraic varieties have strong positivity and convexity properties,
generalizing those of toric varieties and their moment maps. Another special
class, including Gaussian graphical models, are varieties of inverses of
symmetric matrices satisfying linear constraints. We develop a general theory
of exponential varieties, with focus on those defined by hyperbolic polynomials
and their integral representations on the hyperbolicity cone. We compare the
multidegrees and ML degrees of the gradient map for such polynomials.
</summary>
